# SwiftUI Conventions

## View Structure

- Keep views under 200 lines. Extract sub-views into separate files.
- Use `MARK: -` to section views.
- Prefer `@Environment` for DI over singletons.

## Styling

- Use `SCTheme` for spacing, typography, corner radius, colors.
- Do NOT hardcode colors — use `SCTheme.Colors` or `.primary`/`.secondary`.
- Card backgrounds: `GlassCard` or `.ultraThinMaterial`.

## Modifiers

- `.adaptiveGlass()` for glass containers.
- `.applyUserMode()` at root scenes only.
- Platform: `#if os(macOS)` / `#if os(iOS)`.

## Animations

- Default: `SCTheme.Animation.standard` / `.spring` / `.gentle`.
- Always use `shouldReduceMotion` pattern (see `accessibility.mdc`).
